title: Google\Cloud\AppEngine\V1\Application
name: Application
description:
An Application resource contains the top-level configuration of an App Engine application.

Generated from protobuf message google.appengine.v1.Application

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

methods.name: __construct
methods.description: Constructor.

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.name
params.description: Full path to the Application resource in the API. Example: apps/myapp. @OutputOnly

params.name: data.id
params.description: Identifier of the Application resource. This identifier is equivalent to the project ID of the Google Cloud Platform project where you want to deploy your application. Example: myapp.

params.name: data.dispatch_rules
params.description: HTTP path dispatch rules for requests to the application that do not explicitly target a service or version. Rules are order-dependent. Up to 20 dispatch rules can be supported.

params.name: data.auth_domain
params.description: Google Apps authentication domain that controls which users can access this application. Defaults to open access for any Google Account.

params.name: data.location_id
params.description: Location from which this application runs. Application instances run out of the data centers in the specified location, which is also where all of the application's end user content is stored. Defaults to us-central. View the list of supported locations.

params.name: data.code_bucket
params.description: Google Cloud Storage bucket that can be used for storing files associated with this application. This bucket is associated with the application and can be used by the gcloud deployment commands. @OutputOnly

params.name: data.default_cookie_expiration
params.description: Cookie expiration policy for this application.

params.name: data.serving_status
params.description: Serving status of this application.

params.name: data.default_hostname
params.description: Hostname used to reach this application, as resolved by App Engine. @OutputOnly

params.name: data.default_bucket
params.description: Google Cloud Storage bucket that can be used by this application to store content. @OutputOnly

params.name: data.service_account
params.description: The service account associated with the application. This is the app-level default identity. If no identity provided during create version, Admin API will fallback to this one.

params.name: data.gcr_domain
params.description: The Google Container Registry domain used for storing managed build docker images for this application.

params.name: data.database_type
params.description: The type of the Cloud Firestore or Cloud Datastore database associated with this application.

params.name: data.feature_settings
params.description: The feature specific settings to be used in the application.
